commit.message: Bump version number to 25.3.37

Add command line option to specify desired working directory where
to save `gvwstate.dat` file.
Add WORK_DIR parameter to garb.cnf and respective launch scripts.

Refs codership/galera#313

Downgrade message about missing `gvwstate.dat` file to INFO

Refs codership/galera#313
Bump version numbers for 25.3.36

- implement dump_map() method for ring buffer to dump buffer allocatation
   in more detail for debugging purposes.
 - fix pointer advance during initial scan - don't forget to update buffer offset

Refs codership/galera-bugs#789

Amend condition for warning about second segment scan. It should not be
emitted if there was actually no rollover and no second segment.

Refs codership/galera-bugs#784

codership/galera#611 Add all intermediate libs as STATIC

This is required for cmake -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=ON to
work correctly.
Fix INSTALL_SBINDIR parameter in the build script

- Clear traling buffer header at the end of recovered segment to ensure
   rollover when scanning GCache ring buffer.
 - Add additional sanity checks to avoid segfaults if somehow an invalid
   buffer leaks past initial recovery scan.
 - On ring buffer reset remove all seqnos that pointed at ringbuffer from
   seqno2ptr map.

Refs codership/galera-bugs#773

Always allow sending join messages when not in JOINER state

Relaxed condition is required for correct handling of desync counter,
especially in DONOR state: If the DONOR does desync in combination
with SST donation, the gcs_join() calls from resync() and sst_sent() might
come with out of order seqnos, leaving the desync_count in gcs_group
permanently in non-zero value. In this case the node will not become
synced again unless it is temporarily removed from the group.

Refs: MDEV-27459
Bumped version numbers for Galera 3.35
added OpenSSL license if galera uses static SSL libs

Fix static SSL library detection with CMake >= 3.3.1

- Added missing include_directories()
- Remove exact version requirement
Bump version to 3.34

handle exceptions on seqno2ptr_.insert() during GCache recovery: seqnos
there can be absolutely arbitrary and there is no guarantee that insert
will succeed.

Refs codership/galera-bugs#713

Log fatal error and abort instead of throwing an exception in debug
builds in key_set.cpp

use stop_count instead of queue_len to determine if flow control is
active in gcs_replv(). This should allow lagging node (e.g. donor)
to replicate as intended if no flow contorol was activated.

Refs codership/galera-bugs#707

grep away AUTO_INCREMENT values in CREATE TABLE statements for consistency
checking
add seesaw test script that uses sysbench for load generator
reduce the unnecessary GCache debug output verbosity.

if GCache::seqno_release() is called with seqno greater than the seqno
locked for IST, it goes into tight loop until the end of IST. Instead
it should just return. Fixed.

Refs codership/galera-bugs#703
fix debug assert in GCache::disacard_seqno()

codership/galera-bugs#705 Wrong certification results after SST

Certification index was not populated after SST on joiner
for write sets which were contained in the SST but had global
seqno greater than group seqno.

As a fix, do certification for such a write sets to get
certification index populated, but do not apply the write set.

Introduce apply_waits status variable

Count the number of times a thread enters to wait state
in apply monitor. The counter is exposed as a status variable.

ANY IST failure results in state being marked "corrupt", which is too
excessive and may result in the unwarranted fallback to full SST.
During IST invalidate state only in case of trx applying failure, ignore
connection/transfer failures and such.

Refs codership/galera-bugs#681

fix incorrect assert: node in GCS_NODE_STATE_PRIM shoud be able to handle
new primary configuration. Transition PRIM-PRIM is allowed in transition
map.
Also a minor refactoring in mysql/build.sh helper script

Refs codership/galera-bugs#676
codership/galera#558 Restored CK_TIMEOUT_MULTIPLIER in debian rules

Fix CRC32C detection for ARM architectures

Older compilers (GCC 4.8) don't have enough intrinsics exposed
for accelerated CRC32C on ARM. Instead of checking if the compiler
accepts the flag, check that the test code compiles.
Bump version to 25.3.33

codership/galera#210 Clear grastate.dat seqno on joiner before IST

Seqno in grastate.dat was not cleared before processing IST
on joiner. As a result, if the joiner was killed during IST,
it recovered incorrect position from grastate.dat leading
to later failures.

As a fix, set seqno in grastate.dat to WSREP_SEQNO_UNDEFINED
before applying write sets from IST.
